   "source": [
    "# Texture-based separation to refine building meshes \n",
    "\n",
    "## Workflow\n",
    "- Use Texture segmentation to separate the different materials in the meshes\n",
    "- Detect the edges on the texture\n",
    "- Convert the detected edges to hough lines\n",
    "- project the uv coordinates of the mesh onto the plane\n",
    "- Cut the triangles with the detected lines\n",
    "- Define the new faces with the edge boundaries\n",
    "- Segment the different connected zones using region growing\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup\n",
    "Importing the Packages and defining the parameters"

  },

    "## Texture Segmentation\n",
    "\n",
    "- We want to group textures and reduce their detail for better edge detection\n",
    "- use Factorisation based Texture segmentation\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Estimated segment number: 2\n",
      "Texture is segmented\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import segmentationtools.fseg as fseg\n",
    "\n",
    "windowSize = 20\n",
    "omegaVal = 0.2\n",
    "\n",
    "texture = np.asarray(mesh.textures[0])\n",
    "grayTexture = cv2.resize(cv2.cvtColor(texture, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY), (512, 512))\n",
    "# define filter bank and apply to image. for color images, convert rgb to grey scale and then apply filter bank\n",
    "filter_list = [('log', .5, [3, 3]), ('log', 1, [5, 5]),\n",
    "                ('gabor', 1.5, 0), ('gabor', 1.5, math.pi/2), ('gabor', 1.5, math.pi/4), ('gabor', 1.5, -math.pi/4),\n",
    "                ('gabor', 2.5, 0), ('gabor', 2.5, math.pi/2), ('gabor', 2.5, math.pi/4), ('gabor', 2.5, -math.pi/4)\n",
    "                ]\n",
    "filter_out = fseg.image_filtering(grayTexture, filter_list=filter_list)\n",
    "# include original image as one band\n",
    "Ig = np.concatenate((np.float32(grayTexture.reshape((grayTexture.shape[0], grayTexture.shape[1], 1))), filter_out), axis=2)\n",
    "# run segmentation. try different window size, with and without nonneg constraints\n",
    "segmentedTexture = fseg.Fseg(Ig, ws=windowSize, segn=0, omega=omegaVal, nonneg_constraint=False)\n",
    "# Remap to greyscale\n",
    "a = segmentedTexture\n",
    "segmentedMappedTexture = np.round(np.interp(a, (a.min(), a.max()), (0, 255))).astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "print(\"Texture is segmented\")\n",
    "st.show_img(segmentedMappedTexture, bw=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Edge Detection\n",
    "\n",
    "- The patched image is pefect to detect the boundaries of the textures\n",
    "- Use canny or HED edge detection\n",
    "- Find the hough lines to get straight lines in the dtected edges"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Canny"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# perform Canny edge tedection to find sharp gradients\n",
    "dst = cv2.Canny(segmentedMappedTexture, 100, 300, None, 3)\n",
    "dstp = cv2.cvtColor(dst, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)\n",
    "\n",
    "st.show_img(dstp)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Houghlines P"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dstp2 = cv2.cvtColor(dst, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)\n",
    "linesP = cv2.HoughLinesP(dst, 1, np.pi / 360, 30, None, 0, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "if linesP is not None:\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(linesP)):\n",
    "        l = linesP[i][0]\n",
    "        cv2.line(dstp2, (l[0], l[1]), (l[2], l[3]), (0,0,255), 3, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "\n",
    "st.show_img(dstp2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Houghlines"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[[[255.          1.5707964]]]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Lets apply Standard HoughLine transform to detect lines\n",
    "dstp2 = cv2.cvtColor(dst, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)\n",
    "lines = cv2.HoughLines(dst, 2, np.pi / 120, 150, None, 0, 0)\n",
    "print(lines)\n",
    "# Below we will display the result by drawing lines\n",
    "if lines is not None:\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(lines)):\n",
    "        rho = lines[i][0][0]\n",
    "        theta = lines[i][0][1]\n",
    "        a = math.cos(theta)\n",
    "        b = math.sin(theta)\n",
    "        x0 = a * rho\n",
    "        y0 = b * rho\n",
    "        pt1 = (int(x0 + 1000 * (-b)), int(y0 + 1000 * (a)))\n",
    "        pt2 = (int(x0 - 1000 * (-b)), int(y0 - 1000 * (a)))\n",
    "        cv2.line(dstp2, pt1, pt2, (0, 0, 255), 3, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "\n",
    "st.show_img(dstp2)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "## Face Slicing\n",
    "\n",

  {

    "import segmentationtools as st\n",
    "points = []\n",
    "\n",
    "lineNr = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range((int)(len(uvPoints)/3)):\n",
    "    newPoints = st.find_triangle_intersection(uvPoints[3*i:3*i+3], st.get_edge_points(lines[lineNr], segmentedMappedTexture.shape[1], segmentedMappedTexture.shape[0]))\n",
    "    if (newPoints is not None): \n",
    "        points.append(newPoints)\n",
    "\n",
    "points = np.array(points).reshape((-1,2)) #reshape to a nx2 array\n",
    "print(\"The resulting intersection points are: \\n\", points)\n",
    "\n",
    "rho = lines[lineNr][0][0]\n",
    "theta = lines[lineNr][0][1]\n",
    "a = math.cos(theta)\n",
    "b = math.sin(theta)\n",
    "x0 = a * rho\n",
    "y0 = b * rho\n",
    "pt1 = (int(x0 + 1000 * (-b)), int(y0 + 1000 * (a)))\n",
    "pt2 = (int(x0 - 1000 * (-b)), int(y0 - 1000 * (a)))\n",
    "cv2.line(segmentedMappedTexture, pt1, pt2, (0, 0, 255), 3, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.imshow(dstp)\n",
    "for i in range((int)(len(uvPoints)/3)):\n",
    "    plt.fill(*zip(*uvPoints[3*i:3*i+3]), facecolor='none', edgecolor='orangered', linewidth=1)\n",

    "plt.show()\n"
   ]

  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Triangle Slicing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Perform the triangle slicing algorithm for each triangle seperatly\n",
    "uv_coords = np.asarray(mesh.triangle_uvs) * np.array([segmentedMappedTexture.shape[1],segmentedMappedTexture.shape[0]])\n",
    "verts = np.asarray(mesh.vertices)\n",
    "bounds = [segmentedMappedTexture.shape[1], segmentedMappedTexture.shape[0]]\n",
    "edgePoints = st.get_edge_points(lines[lineNr],bounds[0], bounds[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "new_vertices = []\n",
    "new_uvs = []\n",
    "new_triangles = []\n",
    "nrOfVerts = 0\n",
    "nrOfOfVerts = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "for triangle in mesh.triangles:\n",
    "    points_uv = np.array([uv_coords[nrOfOfVerts],uv_coords[nrOfOfVerts+1],uv_coords[nrOfOfVerts+2]])\n",
    "    nrOfOfVerts+=3\n",
    "    points_3d = np.array([verts[triangle[0]],verts[triangle[1]],verts[triangle[2]]])\n",
    "    newTriangles,newTriangles_3d = st.cut_triangle(points_uv, edgePoints, points_3d)\n",
    "    for i in range(len(newTriangles)):\n",
    "        new_vertices.append(newTriangles_3d[i])\n",
    "        new_uvs.append(newTriangles[i] / np.array([segmentedMappedTexture.shape[1],segmentedMappedTexture.shape[0]]))\n",
    "        new_triangles.append([nrOfVerts, nrOfVerts+1, nrOfVerts+2])\n",
    "        nrOfVerts += 3\n"
   ]
  },

    "## Object Segmentation\n",
    "\n",
    "- use the texture blobs and adjacent faces region growing to segment the different objects"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import segmentationtools as st\n",
    "newMesh.textures = [o3d.geometry.Image(cv2.cvtColor(segmentedMappedTexture, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2RGB))]\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# split the mesh based on the texture color and adjacency\n",
    "\n",
    "# open3d adjacency list to get neighbouring verteces"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Face adjacency\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(28, 3, 3)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Prepare the mesh for separation\n",
    "triangle_adjacent = []\n",
    "triangleIndexes = np.full(len(newMesh.triangles),-1)\n",
    "currentIndex = 0\n",
    "nrOfTris = len(newMesh.triangles)\n",
    "\n",
    "mesh_verts = np.asarray(newMesh.vertices)\n",
    "mesh_tris = np.asarray(newMesh.triangles)\n",
    "mesh_uvs = np.asarray(newMesh.triangle_uvs) * np.array([segmentedMappedTexture.shape[1],segmentedMappedTexture.shape[0]])\n",
    "mesh_tris_positions = np.zeros(np.append(np.array(mesh_tris.shape),3))\n",
    "mesh_tris_values = np.full(len(newMesh.triangles),0)\n",
    "for i in range(len(mesh_tris)):\n",
    "    for j in range(3):\n",
    "        mesh_tris_positions[i][j] = mesh_verts[mesh_tris[i][j]]\n",
    "\n",
    "    points_uv = np.array([mesh_uvs[3*i],mesh_uvs[3*i+1],mesh_uvs[3*i+2]])\n",
    "    mesh_tris_values[i] = st.get_tri_pixel_value(points_uv, segmentedMappedTexture )\n",
    "print(mesh_tris_positions.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def mark_adjacent(i,adjacents):\n",
    "    global triangleIndexes\n",
    "    global mesh_tris_values\n",
    "    global mesh_tris_positions\n",
    "    global currentIndex\n",
    "    #compare all adjacents\n",
    "    for idx in adjacents:\n",
    "        if(triangleIndexes[idx] != -1): # ignore the already seglented cases\n",
    "                    continue\n",
    "        if(mesh_tris_values[idx] == mesh_tris_values[i]):\n",
    "                #print(\"Triangle:\", idx, \" \\n value:\", mesh_tris_values[idx])\n",
    "                # both tris have the same pixel value\n",
    "                triangleIndexes[idx] = currentIndex\n",
    "                newAdjacents = st.find_adjacent_triangles(mesh_tris_positions[idx], mesh_tris_positions)\n",
    "                mark_adjacent(idx, newAdjacents)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 35,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",

      "Found all adjacent tris with index:  0\n",

     ]

   ],
   "source": [
    "# check every face\n",
    "for i in range(len(mesh_tris)):\n",
    "    # Check if the triangle is not already segmented\n",
    "    if(triangleIndexes[i] != -1):\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    # give the new itteration a new index nr\n",
    "    triangleIndexes[i] = currentIndex \n",
    "    # look for adjacent triangles with the same color as long as it can\n",
    "    foundAll = False\n",
    "    adjacents = st.find_adjacent_triangles(mesh_tris_positions[i], mesh_tris_positions)\n",
    "    mark_adjacent(i,adjacents)\n",
    "    print(\"Found all adjacent tris with index: \", currentIndex)   \n",
    "    currentIndex +=1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(triangleIndexes)"

    "import open3d\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "mesh = open3d.geometry.TriangleMesh()\n",
    "np_vertices = newMesh.vertices\n",
    "np_triangles = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(len(triangleIndexes)):\n",
    "    if(triangleIndexes[i] == 0):\n",
